-- Bike and Level check to get acces to Area 1 | Nested if-statements

playerLevel = 11
hasBike = true
area1Level = 10

-- Nested if-statements

function enterArea1()
   if playerLevel >= area1Level then
     if hasBike then
        print("You can enter the area!")
     else
        print("You must have a bike!")
     end
   else
      print("You must be at least level: " .. area1Level)
   end
end

enterArea1()


________________________________________________________________
________________________________________________________________
________________________________________________________________

Output:

You can enter the area!           (if playeLevel > 10 & hasBike is true)
You must have a bike!             (if playeLevel > 10 & hasBike is false)
You must be at least level: 10    (if playerLevel < 10 | 10 because area1Level = 10)
